  notes       = {Two key findings. First, entrepreneurial team formation is driven by homophily. Second, diversity in entrepreneurial teams is associated with worse performance, though attenuated when members voluntarily select into teams. This suggests that while homophily is a strong driver of team formation, diversity may not always lead to better outcomes in entrepreneurial settings. Can cite this to show ubiquity of homophily in team formation and its implications for performance.}
